# Google Ads provider

## Tool naming

All tools prefixed `google_`. Register in `tools.go`; implement in `accounts.go`, `reports.go`, `report_queries.go`, or `reports_legacy.go`.

## Gateway proxy

Use `proxy.go` / `googleGateway.requestJSON` — never call Google Ads directly. All requests go through mcp-ads-manager with the user's OAuth token and `developer-token` header (gateway adapter).

## MCC / login-customer-id

- `customer_id`: account being queried (client or standalone).
- `login_customer_id`: manager (MCC) id when querying a client under an MCC.
- `google_resolve_customer` returns both when match is under a manager.

## GAQL

- Shared builders in `gaql.go`.
- Date filters: `segments.date` with `YYYY-MM-DD`.
- Enum filters: uppercase unquoted (`ENABLED`).
- Report limits: default 500, max 1000.

## Schemas and agent docs

- Input JSON schemas: `schemas.go`.
- Long descriptions: `schema_docs.go`.
- Product matrix: [docs/google-ads-tools.md](../../docs/google-ads-tools.md).

## Tests

Add `*_test.go` for GAQL builders, parsers, and account matching. Run:

```bash
go test ./internal/provider/googleads/...
```

## UI catalog sync

After adding a tool, update mcp-ads-manager `apps/web/lib/mcp-provider-tools.ts` (`ProviderAgentToolsCollapsible` on `/connections`).
